most_relevant.description: A must-do in Warsaw! We bought our tickets 2 hours prior and went in the evening when the sun started setting and the view was breathtaking! We stayed for a while until it was completely dark out and the views were just as beautiful. Highly recommend if you’re visiting Warsaw. The tickets are not so expensive either - 28 Złoty per person (23 for students).

The Palace of Culture and Science in Warsaw offers an absolutely breathtaking view from the top! Standing at the observation deck, you get a panoramic view of the entire city, and it’s simply magnificent. The combination of modern skyscrapers and historic architecture creates a stunning contrast that you can’t miss. It’s a must-visit spot, especially if you want to truly appreciate the beauty of Warsaw from above. The experience is unforgettable and worth every moment!

The Palace of Culture and Science was a great experience! There were so many interesting things to see and explore, making it a fascinating visit. The entrance fee was very affordable, which added to the value of the experience.

However, we were a bit disappointed that we couldn’t go to the top to enjoy the view, which we had been looking forward to. That said, the overall experience was still really enjoyable and well worth the visit.

The Palace of Culture and Science in Warsaw is a stunning example of Soviet-era monumental architecture. Built with grandeur and the intention to impress, it stands as a symbol of power and ambition. However, its current state feels as if it has been passed down to distant relatives from the countryside – left with a grand apartment from a professor and now trying to make the most of it, but only on their own level. The once majestic hall with its grand chandeliers and marble ceilings now hosts events like a “Japanese Culture Festival” – but looking at the pictures, only about 5% of it feels genuinely Japanese, mostly limited to Japanese alcohol and some “Japanese” toys made in China. It’s sad to see such an impressive space being used in this way, but the place is still filled with visitors, all eating and enjoying themselves. This is the culture now, and unfortunately, the palace reflects that.

P.S. A tip for those wanting to visit the observation deck: the line for online tickets is always much shorter. You can simply buy your ticket on your phone while waiting. Enjoy!

The Palace of Culture and Science in Warsaw offers a breathtaking panoramic view of the city. While the experience is remarkable, be prepared for windy and cold conditions at the top. Despite the chill, it’s a must-visit place.

It’s truly a beautiful place in the day and at night. Viewing Warsaw skyline from the observation deck is a must. It’s on the 30th floor. You get a 360 view of city. Just know it stays packed with people. Make sure you walk around the building to see the giant statues.

I’ve been coming to the observation deck of the palace for 3 or 4 years now. It never fails to amaze me, the Warsaw skyline from the view of the palace is stunning. Every year I see a new skyscraper added to the skyline. The queue can be long sometimes, especially around sunset. It’s always a good idea to come at least 1 hour before the sun sets on the horizon to have enough time to appreciate it. I also reccomend to buy tickets online to save even more time. There’s also tons of other facilities in the building such as a university, a club, bar, theatre, museum, and much more. My university once had a fancy dance and ball here in one of the venues you can rent out. This is a multi function facility. Come check it out!

We have visited it at dusk and were a bit worried that may be it would be too dark to see anything but it appeared to be a cool view with all the night lights and illumination. So we enjoyed it and were not disappointed.
Better buy tickets online so that not to wait in line.
Price: 28zl
